-- Indonesian Equity Movers: Bakrieland, Bumi Resources, Panorama
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-04-23T09:31:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/indonesian-equity-movers-bakrieland-medco-energi-panorama.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite Index (JCI)  fell 0.6 percent to 4,155.49,
the biggest drop since April 4.  Bakrie Group related companies:  PT Bakrieland Development (ELTY) 
, a property developer, retreated 5.6 percent to 118
rupiah,  PT Bakrie Sumatera Plantations (UNSP)  , a palm oil and
rubber producer, lost 3.3 percent to 295 rupiah.  PT Bumi
Resources (BUMI)  , the nation’s largest coal producer, sank
7.4 percent to 1,990 rupiah, the most since Nov. 1.  Indonesia ’s Bakrie family received a default notice from
creditors on a $437 million loan after a drop in the shares of
London-listed mining company Bumi Plc that guaranteed the
facility, the Financial Times reported. PT Bakrie & Brothers
Finance Director Eddy Soeparno denied the report, saying the
company didn’t receive a default notice.  PT Bank Mandiri (BMRI)  , Indonesia’s biggest bank by
assets, fell 2.8 percent to 6,950 rupiah after announcing a
dividend payout of 104.97 rupiah a share, compared with 120.60
rupiah last year.  PT Panorama Transportasi (WEHA)  , a tour-bus and taxi
operator, advanced 1.2 percent to 167 rupiah, the highest close
since Feb. 14. The company said it plans to offer 100 billion
rupiah ($10.9 million) of three-year bonds on May 10 and May 11
to repay bank loans and purchase new vehicles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
